The paper discusses the development of a recommendation system for sightseeing information on SNS, which involves user participatory sensing and smartphone applications. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) and Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC). The paper also proposes the use of a simulation system for multi-agent systems with altruistic behaviors, which falls under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the revitalization of the SNS community, which may fall under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) as it involves ensuring the security and safety of the community.
